@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Home Page";
}
<div style="position: relative">
    <img class="header-mast" src="~/Content/img/masthead.PNG" />
    <div class="entry-form">
        <div class="enter-here">
            <form class="form-horizontal">
                <h3 style="margin-top: 0px;">Get the Free White Paper</h3>
                <div>Your Name*</div>
                <input class="form-control" type="text" name="name" required="" />
                <div>Email Address*</div>
                <input class="form-control" type="email" name="email" required=" " />
                <div>Company Name</div>
                <input class="form-control" type="text" name="company" />
                <div>Phone Number</div>
                <input class="form-control" type="tel" name="phone" />
                <input style="margin-top:10px;" type="submit" value="SUBMIT" class="btn btn-block btn-warning" />
            </form>
        </div>
        <div class="thank-you" style="display: none;">
            <h3 style="margin-top: 0px;">Thank you</h3>
            <p>
                The Free White Paper has been sent.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row break text-center">
    <div class="col-sm-4">
        <img src="~/Content/img/hardhat.jpg" />
        <h3>Reduce Operational Cost</h3>
        <p class="text-muted">
            By upgrading to Windows Server 2012 you will not only reduce operational costs, but also increase efficiencies and you will gain the ability to be cloud-ready.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-4">
        <img src="~/Content/img/evilman.jpg" />
        <h3>Maintain Compliance</h3>
        <p class="text-muted">
            Don't jeopardize corporate compliance by allowing an unsupported version of Windows in your data center. On July 15 compliance will no longer be attainable with a Windows 2003 server environment.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-4">
        <img src="~/Content/img/prettylady.jpg" />
        <h3>Improve Productivity</h3>
        <p class="text-muted">
            Upgrading to Windows Server 2012 will improve employee productivity, and give the ability to implement cost-effective backup and disaster recovery solutions.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="row break">
    <div class="col-lg-12 text-right future">
        Worldwide, 57% of the installed base of x86 servers (a total of 13 million servers) are still running Windows Server 2003. With hundreds of new features in Windows Server 2012,
        upgrading to the most modern version of Windows Server can deliver significant business benefits, efficiencies and drive customer relationships.
    </div>
</div>

@section scripts
{
    <script>
        $(document).ready(function () {
            var form = $('.enter-here form');
            form.on('submit', function (event) {
                event.preventDefault();
                var codes = form.serialize();
                $.post('/home?' + codes);
                $('.enter-here').hide();
                $('.thank-you').show();
            });
        });

    </script>
}
